=== Schema Changes ===
deals table: 8 nullable columns added
  dispo_asking_price numeric NULL
  dispo_intersection text NULL
  dispo_closing_date date NULL
  dispo_description text NULL
  dispo_comparables text NULL
  dispo_media_url text NULL (https:// with valid host required or empty/null)
  dispo_market_value_estimate numeric NULL
  dispo_below_market_override numeric NULL

Below-market derivation: COALESCE(dispo_below_market_override, dispo_market_value_estimate - dispo_asking_price)

=== RPCs Added ===
update_dispo_packet_v1(p_deal_id uuid, p_fields jsonb)
  VOLATILE SECURITY DEFINER
  GRANT EXECUTE to authenticated only
  Guards: require_min_role_v1('member'), current_tenant_id(), auth.uid(), check_workspace_write_allowed_v1()
  p_fields patch semantics: omit=unchanged, explicit null=clear, empty string=normalize to NULL
  Unknown keys: VALIDATION_ERROR
  Numeric/date/URL validation: envelope-safe
  dispo_media_url: https:// with valid host required, regex enforced
  Stage guard: dispo/under_contract only; other stages return CONFLICT
  Writes deal_activity_log (packet_update) on success
  Cross-tenant: NOT_FOUND
  Non-member: NOT_AUTHORIZED

lookup_share_token_public_v1(p_token text)
  STABLE SECURITY DEFINER
  GRANT EXECUTE to anon AND authenticated
  No current_tenant_id() required -- token is authorization mechanism
  Resolution: validate format -> hash -> lookup share_tokens by token_hash -> check revoked -> check expired -> check workspace subscription (from token row)
  Returns only allowlisted buyer-facing packet fields
  No exact address, no seller/internal fields
  Identical NOT_FOUND envelope for all failure cases (no existence leak)
  tenant_context_exempt in definer_allowlist.json

lookup_share_token_v1 unchanged -- authenticated tenant-scoped contract preserved

=== QA Architecture Ruling ===
Per QA ruling 2026-05-25: share token lookup split by caller class:
  lookup_share_token_v1: authenticated, tenant-scoped internal lookup (unchanged)
  lookup_share_token_public_v1: public buyer-facing lookup, token is authorization
Future share-token read RPCs must preserve this split unless QA explicitly approves a contract migration.

